Implement Atoi (String to Integer Conversion)
ðŸ“Œ Problem Statement

Given a string s, convert it into a 32-bit signed integer without using any built-in conversion functions.

The conversion follows the rules of the atoi() function.

ðŸ§  Conversion Rules

Ignore leading whitespaces

Determine the sign (+ or -), default is positive

Read digits until a non-digit character is found

If no digits are present, return 0

Clamp the result within the 32-bit signed integer range

